1. Fastq file QC:
(1) FastQC: http://www.bioinformatics.babraham.ac.uk/projects/fastqc/
(2) FastQ Screen: http://www.bioinformatics.babraham.ac.uk/projects/fastq_screen/
(3) MultiQC: https://github.com/ewels/MultiQC , https://pypi.python.org/pypi/multiqc/

2. Remove Duplicates based on FASTQ files
(1) Clumpify in BBMap: https://www.biostars.org/p/225338/ , https://sourceforge.net/projects/bbmap/

3. Trim and Filter
(1) Trimmomatic: http://www.usadellab.org/cms/?page=trimmomatic
(2) Trim Galore: http://www.bioinformatics.babraham.ac.uk/projects/trim_galore/

4. Reads mapping (Mappers or Aligners)
(1) DNA: BWA-mem and BWA-aln: https://github.com/lh3/bwa
(2) RNA: STAR or hisat2

5. Mapped reads QC
(1) SAMstat: https://sourceforge.net/projects/samstat/
(2) qualimap: http://qualimap.bioinfo.cipf.es/
(3) Picard: https://github.com/broadinstitute/picard

6. Some fancy R packges
(1) ggpubr: CNS plot additional with statistic test p value.
(2) ggstatsplot: plot with p value.
(3) ggsci: color selection for journals.
